{{Infobox building | name = Onomichi City Museum of Art | native_name = 尾道市立美術館 | image = Onomichi City Museum of Art02s3200.jpg | caption = | cost = | owner = | address = 17−19 Nishitsuchidō-chō | location_town = [[Onomichi, Hiroshima|Onomichi]], [[Hiroshima Prefecture]] | location_country = [[Japan]] | coordinates = {{coord|34.409917|N|133.195800|E|display=title,inline|format=dms|type:landmark_region:JP_scale:10000}} | opened_date = 1980 | inauguration_date = | renovation_date = 11 January 2003 | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | other_dimensions = | floor_count = | floor_area = | architect = [[Tadao Ando]] | architecture_firm = | url = {{URL|1=http://www7.city.onomichi.hiroshima.jp/?page_id=2}} }}
{{nihongo|'''Onomichi City Museum of Art'''|尾道市立美術館|Onomichi shiritsu bijutsukan}} opened in [[Senkō-ji (Onomichi)|Senkō-ji]] Park in [[Onomichi, Hiroshima|Onomichi]], [[Hiroshima Prefecture]], Japan, in 1980. The Museum reopened to a design by [[Tadao Ando]] in 2003. The collection includes works by {{nihongo|[[Kobayashi Wasaku]]|[[:ja:小林和作|小林和作]]}} and {{nihongo|[[Wada Eisaku]]|[[:ja:和田英作|和田英作]]}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://bunka.nii.ac.jp/museums/detail/13079 |script-title=ja:尾道市立美術館 |trans-title=Onomichi City Museum of Art |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=18 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kankou.pref.hiroshima.jp/sys/data?page-id=5356 |script-title=ja:尾道市立美術館 |trans-title=Onomichi City Museum of Art |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Hiroshima Prefecture]] |accessdate=18 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www7.city.onomichi.hiroshima.jp/?page_id=2 |script-title=ja:美術館について |trans-title=About the Museum |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Onomichi, Hiroshima|Onomichi City]] |accessdate=18 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www7.city.onomichi.hiroshima.jp/?page_id=70 |script-title=ja:コレクション |trans-title=Collection |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Onomichi, Hiroshima|Onomichi City]] |accessdate=18 October 2015}}</ref>
The museum has become notable on the Internet for being visited on a regular basis by two [[cats]], whom the museum guards have to repeatedly turn away due to the museum's strict "no animals" policy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedodo.com/close-to-home/cats-visiting-japanese-art-museum-turned-away |title=These Two Cats Won't Give Up On Trying To Enter Japanese Art Museum |last=Fenn |first=Lily |date=11 February 2018 |website=The Dodo |access-date=14 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Oona |first=McGee |date=11 July 2016 |title=Art-loving feline attempts to enter cat exhibition at Hiroshima museum |url=https://soranews24.com/2016/07/11/art-loving-feline-attempts-to-enter-cat-exhibition-at-hiroshima-museum |work=SoraNews24 |location=Tokyo |access-date= 14 November 2018}}</ref>
