The '''Video Game Masters Tournament''' was an event that was created in 1983 by [[Twin Galaxies]] to generate world record high scores for the 1984 U.S. Edition of the [[Guinness World Records|Guinness Book of World Records]].<ref>{{cite journal|title='86 Video Game Masters Tourney Set for June 27-29|journal=Cash Box|date=June 28, 1986|volume=50|issue=2|page=34|url=http://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Cash-Box/80s/1986/CB-1986-06-28.pdf|accessdate=August 20, 2017}}</ref> It was the most prestigious contest of that era and the only one that the Guinness book looked to for verified world records on video games at the time.{{cn|date=August 2017}} This contest was conducted under the joint efforts of Twin Galaxies and the [[U.S. National Video Game Team]] in 1983, 1984 and 1985 and by the U.S. National Video Game Team alone in 1986 and 1987.<ref>[http://www.twingalaxies.com/index.aspx?c=18&id=705 They're Masters of Video Games - Spokesman-Review, Spokane, WA - August 24, 1983] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071208034852/http://www.twingalaxies.com/index.aspx?c=18&id=705 |date=December 8, 2007 }}</ref>
During its first year, 1983, the event was called the North America Video Game Challenge (State Teams Tournament), but was changed to the Video Game Masters Tournament by the second year.<ref>[http://www.twingalaxies.com/images/generalinfo/State_Teams_Tournment.jpg State Teams Tournament - Poster, August 24-28, 1983] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100102160954/http://www.twingalaxies.com/images/generalinfo/State_Teams_Tournment.jpg |date=January 2, 2010 }}</ref>
In order to administer the contest, Twin Galaxies appointed the U.S. National Video Game Team to the task of collecting and verifying scores from the eight cities that participated in the 1983 edition of this event. The cities were Seattle, Washington; Lake Odessa, Michigan; Coeur D'Alene, Idaho; Omaha, Nebraska; Dayton, Ohio; San Jose, California; Upland, California and Chicago, Illinois.<ref>[http://twingalaxies.com/index.aspx?c=18&id=1032 U.S.Video Team Forming; Plans Call for Match with Japan - RePlay Magazine, October, 1983] {{dead link|date=September 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>
The 1984 event was also conducted in eight cities while the 1985 event was conducted in 35 cities.<ref>[http://www.twingalaxies.com/index.aspx?c=18&id=1411 1985 Video Game Masters Tournament - Computer entertainment Magazine, July, 1985] {{dead link|date=September 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref><ref name="twingalaxies.com">[http://www.twingalaxies.com/images/generalinfo/1985vgmt.gif 1985 Video Game Masters Tournament - Poster, June, 1985]</ref>
